{
  "texts": [
    "It will be based on the results of [Moc25] and formulated in the language of Stokes local systems: If (E, ∇) is an algebraic connection on the affine line satisfying our assumptions, and if (E, ∇) is its Fourier transform, the algorithm allows us to determine the Stokes local system of (E, ∇) from of the one of (E, ∇) in a completely explicit, algorithmic and topological way.",
    "While we refer the reader to the main body of the article for the fully detailed statements, let us sketch the main ideas underlying the algorithm and its structure.",
    "It is well-known that the formal data, i.e.",
    "the Levelt-Turrittin normal form, of (E, ∇) are determined by those of (E, ∇): This is expressed by the stationary phase formula [Mal91, Sab08, Fa09], which states in particular that the exponents of (E, ∇) are related to those of (E, ∇) via a Legendre transform.",
    "Usually, the Legendre transform is viewed as providing a bijection between the sets of exponents before and after the Fourier transform."
  ]
}